National Museum 360 Viewer


REQUIREMENTS

    * nodejs


GETTING STARTED

    > git clone git@github.com:GuardianInteractive/national-museum-360.git
    > cd national-museum-360
    > npm install
    > grunt

DEVELOPER DEPENDENCIES

    * imagemagick
    * avconv (or ffmpeg)

EXTRACTING VIDEO FRAMES

    > avconv -i videos/video_file.MTS -r 1 -vsync 1 -filter:v "crop=w:h:x:y" -qscale:v 1 -f image2 images/filename-%03d.png


RESIZE AND OPTIMIZE IMAGES

    > mogrify -path src/images/path/ -format jpg -unsharp 0.7x0.7+0.6+0 -strip -interlace Plane -resize x640 -filter Lanczos -quality 55% -black-threshold 4% ./images/input/*.png